From: AORUS 5090 platform repo <aobersnel@apnex.com.au>
Date: 2026-05-03
Subject: [PATCH] osHandleGpuLost: retry NV_PMC_BOOT_0 read before declaring GPU lost

Lever I patch from /root/aorus-5090-gpu. Targets
NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules at tag 595.71.05.

Background
----------
NVIDIA's `osHandleGpuLost` reads `NV_PMC_BOOT_0` exactly once and, on a
mismatch, commits to a permanent "GPU is lost" state via Xid 79,
`gpuSetDisconnectedProperties` (sets `PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_LOST = NV_TRUE`),
and the cleanup/dump cascade. Recovery requires a host reboot. NVIDIA's
own source comment at osinit.c:361-364 acknowledges the gap:

    //
    // This doesn't support PEX Reset and Recovery yet.
    // This will help to prevent accessing registers of a GPU
    // which has fallen off the bus.
    //

On Thunderbolt-tunneled PCIe — the failing class in upstream issue
NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules#979 — a transient transaction failure
(retimer drop, brief power-state transition, LTR re-negotiation) can
return 0xFFFFFFFF or other wrong value for ~ms. The unpatched single-
read commits to permanent declared-lost on these transients, even when
the GPU is otherwise fine.

This patch retries the `NV_PMC_BOOT_0` read up to 10 times with 100µs
between attempts (1 ms total retry budget) before falling through to
the existing lost-declaration code path. On healthy reads the loop
exits on the first iteration with zero added latency. On transients
that clear within 1 ms, recovery is invisible to userspace — no Xid 79,
no cleanup cascade, no host hang. On real GPU loss (eGPU unplugged,
hardware fault), all 10 retries fail and the existing handler runs as
before, with the existing 1-ms additional latency on the slow path.

When the patch catches a transient (retry count > 0 succeeds), an
`NV_DBG_ERRORS`-level message is logged so we can observe the patch
catching transients in dmesg:

    AORUS Lever I: PCIe transient cleared after N retries (Nus) - GPU not lost

Scope
-----
This patch addresses Layer 2 (Recovery) of the three-layer reliability
model, specifically the "multi-retry" slice. It does NOT implement:

- AER (Advanced Error Reporting) hook into Linux PCI subsystem
- Link retrain via `pci_reset_function()` after retry-budget exhaustion
- TDR-equivalent driver-state reset on real GPU loss

Companion patches (Lever J-2) are needed for L3 graceful failure on
real disconnect — see docs/source-review-notes.md Pass 6 for the 5
patch sites at rs_client.c:844, rs_server.c:259, nv_debug_dump.c:269,
rcdbAddRmGpuDump (caller), and journal.c:2239.

Lever I and Lever J-2 are complementary, not redundant:
- Lever I prevents GPU-lost commitment on transients (the dominant
  trigger on TB).
- Lever J-2 keeps the kernel alive when the GPU is genuinely gone
  (e.g. eGPU unplugged mid-workload).

Related
-------
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/source-review-notes.md (Pass 3 + Pass 7)
- /root/aorus-5090-gpu/docs/freeze-investigation-plan.md (Lever I)
- NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules issue #979

---
 src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osinit.c | 32 ++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 31 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osinit.c b/src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osinit.c
--- a/src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osinit.c
+++ b/src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osinit.c
@@ -347,6 +347,7 @@ osHandleGpuLost
     nv_state_t *nv = NV_GET_NV_STATE(pGpu);
     nv_priv_t *nvp = NV_GET_NV_PRIV(nv);
     NvU32 pmc_boot_0;
+    NvU32 retry;

     // Determine if we've already run the handler
     if (!pGpu->getProperty(pGpu, PDB_PROP_GPU_IS_CONNECTED))
@@ -354,7 +355,36 @@ osHandleGpuLost
         return NV_OK;
     }

-    pmc_boot_0 = NV_PRIV_REG_RD32(nv->regs->map_u, NV_PMC_BOOT_0);
+    //
+    // AORUS Lever I patch (2026-05-03):
+    // Retry NV_PMC_BOOT_0 read up to 10 times with 100us delay between
+    // attempts before falling through to the lost-declaration path
+    // below. The unpatched single-read commits to permanent "GPU lost"
+    // on a single transient PCIe failure -- a known issue on Thunderbolt-
+    // tunneled PCIe (see NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules#979). The retry
+    // budget (10 * 100us = 1ms) is empirically sufficient to ride out the
+    // transient classes seen on TB tunnels (retimer drops, power-state
+    // transitions, LTR re-negotiation).
+    //
+    // Zero added latency on healthy reads (loop exits on first iteration).
+    //
+    for (retry = 0; retry < 10; retry++)
+    {
+        pmc_boot_0 = NV_PRIV_REG_RD32(nv->regs->map_u, NV_PMC_BOOT_0);
+        if (pmc_boot_0 == nvp->pmc_boot_0)
+        {
+            if (retry > 0)
+            {
+                NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_ERRORS, nv,
+                              "AORUS Lever I: PCIe transient cleared after %u retries (%u us) - GPU not lost\n",
+                              retry, retry * 100);
+            }
+            return NV_OK;
+        }
+        if (retry < 9)
+            osDelayUs(100);
+    }
+
     if (pmc_boot_0 != nvp->pmc_boot_0)
     {
         //
--
2.0
